cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the citation patterns of journals in computer science and related fields, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and computers and society (cs.CY). These sub-categories are relevant because they cover topics related to scholarly communication, bibliometrics, and the impact of publications, which are central to the paper's analysis.
